text:
so I have the rich text module within a td. The td has styling of it's own which I would be more than happy with the whole thing just adopting. So I can just add something like:
```&lt;style data-hse-inline-css="true"&gt;
p{
margin-bottom:0px !important;
}
&lt;/style&gt;```

The id tag gets added to the style tag, actually — not sure that it’s valid markup, but it doesn’t matter because it gets stripped in the parse phase. So, something like this:
```&lt;style id="hs-inline-css" data-hse-inline="true"&gt;
  .containing-element-class p {
     margin-bottom: 0 !important;
   }
&lt;/style&gt;```
